Instructions for a linux install (windows coming soon):

1. Install the Go 1 language: 

http://golang.org/doc/install

2. Grab this code with: 

git clone https://code.google.com/p/ricbot

3. Set up the gopath, pointing it to wherever you downloaded the code:

export GOPATH=/home/ricbit/ricbot

4. Compile ricbot:

go build ricbot.go

5. Download gogui:

http://gogui.sourceforge.net/

6. Launch gogui, then select on its menu: 

Program, New Program, and then point it to the ricbot binary you compiled.
